rComments: He says a lot of "um"s in his lectures. He has a really good personality and likes to joke around with his students. But, for exams he tests a lot of unnecessary details from one chapter and tests the general ideas from another chapter. The lectures don't correspond to the textbook and you don't know what you'll be tested on. Hes pretty chill tho.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Fun lecturer. Goes on tangents sometimes but interesting. Passionate about research and doesn't dumb things down. If you're serious about personality psychology, you will enjoy his class.
